text: Alloinay is a commune in the department of Deux-Sèvres, western France. The municipality was established on 1 January 2017 by merger of the former communes of Gournay-Loizé (the seat) and Les Alleuds.Arrêté préfectoral 8 April 2016 == See also == *Communes of the Deux-Sèvres department == References == Category:Communes of Deux-Sèvres Category:Populated places established in 2017
title: Alloinay
